1 INTRODUCTION
"Active Galactic Nuclei (AGN) are believed to be powered
by the accretion of matter on to super massive black hole
(SMBH; 106 − 1010 M�) located at the center of galaxies
(Lynden-Bell 1969; Salpeter 1964). This extreme physical
process is responsible for the radiation we receive from AGN
over a wide range of energies predominantly emitted in X-
ray, UV and optical wavelengths. The SMBH is surrounded
by the accretion disk and the optical/UV emission seen in
the spectral energy distribution of an AGN is attributed
to the thermal emission from the accretion disk. Farther"
